   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ With GOP leadership _ pardon the oxymoron _
bypassing committee hearings and going straight to the floor, the
House this week will debate and vote on fake gun control and
throwback juvenile crime measures. With luck, the whole mess will
politically self-destruct. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent
for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ The way I figure it, I've got 17 hours to see
what Y2K is doing to the rest of the world before it gets to me.
Look, the calendar turns to 2000 somewhere out in the middle of the
Pacific 17 hours before it turns in the Eastern U.S. If computers
are going to crash, if ATM machines are going to fail, if airplanes
are going to fall, I'll know in plenty of time and can adjust _ or
panic, if that is preferable. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for
Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ The traveler began to speak: ``The
cost-cutting airline executive started by getting rid of
complimentary meals in coach. The savings, when annualized, were
