<P>
   AIR-FORCE-TRAINING (San Antonio) _ Reacting to criticism that
basic training isn't tough enough, the Air Force this fall will
require its recruits at Lackland Air Force Base to endure ``Warrior
Week,'' a seven-day test of war-fighting skills. The idea behind
Warrior Week is to create an Air Force ``that is more ready to go
to a forward-deployed location and live in an austere
environment,'' according to Lt. Col. Steven Ray. By SIG
CHRISTENSON.
</P>
<P>
   GRIEF-STUDIES (Albany, N.Y.) _ After years of learning about
death and dying through their work with hospice patients, two women
are developing a college curriculum leading to a certificate in
bereavement. The 15-credit certification program is aimed at
health-care professionals, educators and others seeking to work in
the field of bereavement services. By PAUL GRONDAHL.
</P>
<P>
   PRESIDIO-LUCAS (San Francisco) _ ``Star Wars'' mastermind George
Lucas has won approval to transform 23 acres inside the Presidio
into a grassy campus for more than 2,000 technical wizards of the
Lucasfilm empire in the new Presidio national park. By TYCHE
HENDRICKS.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CAREERS (San Francisco) _ The singles champions in the French
Open Tennis tournament, Andre Agassi and Steffi Graf, are both 29
years old, which is as rare these days as a Silicon Valley company
hiring two 55-year-old computer programmers. We're in an era in
which youth is served _ and age is smashed back in your face. By
DAVE MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-HANNIBAL _ The iron law of sequels, in books or movies,
boils down to this: To succeed, they must exceed. Thomas Harris
could be the poster boy for the law of sequel success. ``Hannibal''
(Delacorte Press, $27.95), the just-released continuation of his
best-selling 1988 ``Silence of the Lambs'' (itself a sequel to the
1981 ``Red Dragon''), fairly bursts with lurid violence and sleek,
brainy bad guys. By FRITZ LANHAM.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   POSTPARTUM-BLUES (Albany, N.Y.) _ For one in every 10 new
mothers, the months after delivery offer a profound sense of
sadness, hopelessness, mood swings and insomnia. Postpartum
depression, as it's known, is fairly common, though not well
understood and often underdiagnosed. By SYLVIA WOOD.
</P>
<P>
   CAT-B&AMP;B (Queensbury, N.Y.) _ Cat owners who don't want to
consign their beloved kitty to a standard-issue kennel can bring
their feline friends to a ``cat bed and breakfast.'' Kip and Jean
Grant of Queensbury, owners of four cats, designed the Country
Kitty B &AMP; B to provide ``an affordable alternative for cat owners
who must decide how and where to care for their pets while they're
away from home.'' By BETSY FELDSTEIN.
</P>
