</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CONN (Greenwich, Conn.) _ George W. Bush is collecting
hometowns almost as fast as his father did. The ruling class of
Greenwich, Conn., plans to welcome him as a favorite son at a
fund-raiser tonight, even though he jokingly disparages his Yankee
roots. But this is Bush country, and the dinner is expected to
raise $1 million, a record for a political event in Connecticut.
Organizers say people are calling up, unasked, hoping to give
money. With voices from donors who know the family, which seems
like just about all of them. By Mike Allen.
</P>
<P>
   GA-RAPE-DNA (Atlanta) _ Calvin Johnson, a black man convicted of
rape 17 years ago in Clayton County, Ga., will be freed after new
DNA testing shows he could not have been the attacker. His case was
taken up by the Innocence Project, run by Barry Scheck, Peter
Neufeld, etc., who say Johnson has been in prison longer than any
of the 40 prisoners they've exonerated. By David Firestone.
</P>
