   UNEXPLORED LANDS: It's true that explorers have reached the
world's highest mountain (Everest, 29,029 feet) and the deepest
ocean (Mariana Trench, in the Pacific, 35,797 feet). And this might
suggest that the Earth is all explored. But at the dawn of a new
millennium, it's amazing to learn that some parts of the world
still haven't been charted. What are the unexplored places and why
hasn't anyone reached them yet? (Includes a 4-column color map
illustration.)
</P>
