   TRAFFIC: Are we there yet? Experts say that vacation trip _ hey,
cut that out! _ may take a little longer this summer thanks to the
$3 billion in highway improvements Congress passed last year. In
fact, expect construction every 40 miles or so. Besides danger _ a
lot of rear end accidents when cars suddenly slow down and highway
workers run over _ it's going to be quite an inconvenience since
lower gasoline prices are expected to boost travel. We check
construction in Missouri and Kansas and major interstates in the
region to localize so the traveling consumer knows what to expect.
Ruth Igoe with staff inserts. 25. Photo. Graphic.
</P>
