<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By FRANK J. PRIAL   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Gewuerztraminer Herrenweg Turckheim 1996, Zind-Humbrecht,
Alsace, France. About $29.
</P>
<P>
   A cool late summer and early fall in 1996 resulted in unusually
high acidity in many Alsatian wines. For producers who make leaner,
drier wines, this could be a problem, but I must admit I actually
enjoyed the touch of sharpness in this gewuerztraminer.
</P>
<P>
   The Humbrechts make some of the richest, most intense white
wines in the world, many of them truly masterpieces. But their
fullness and power can at times be almost overwhelming. They are
wines to sip slowly and wonder at.
</P>
<P>
   This gewuerztraminer has all the fruit and concentrated bouquet
one expects from Zind-Humbrecht, but with an added jolt of
freshness that makes it almost irresistible. The higher acidity
should help the wine age well.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-15-99 1452EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
