<HEADER>
A6112 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TV-REALWORLD-REVIEW-S     06-15 0535
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-REALWORLD-REVIEW-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
YOUNG HEDONISTS GET `REAL' ON MTV 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOHN CARMAN  
 c.1999, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   You know it'll be a good year on ``The Real World'' when you
feel an instant dislike for the vile youths onscreen.
</P>
<P>
   Say (set ital)aloha(end ital) and settle in. Off with your
clothes.
</P>
<P>
   This season, Honolulu is home base for the perversely
entertaining MTV series. The debauchery begins Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Here comes Teck, 22, by appearances a younger version of Dennis
Rodman. He's vanning to his new beachfront digs with one of his new
housemates, Ruthie, 21.
</P>
<P>
   Ruthie was raised in a Hawaiian foster home by a strict Filipino
family, but she's got a curvy Polynesian look going.
</P>
<P>
   Teck approves. They've just met, and he's already got action in
mind. But wait. Ruthie's got a girlfriend. A (set ital)girl(end
ital)friend, man.
</P>
<P>
   Ruthie, on Teck: ``He's got some game. He won't get it from me,
but he'll get it.''
</P>
<P>
   So Teck settles for getting naked the moment he arrives at the
``Real World'' house. Ruthie, too. They're both judicious blurs as
they strip and leap giddily into the outdoor swimming pool.
</P>
<P>
   Teck and Ruthie are thus occupied when their five housemates
arrive one and two at a time. Teck is forever standing in the pool
to extend his hand, which apparently outdistances his other blurred
appendage.
</P>
<P>
   Newly arrived housemate Amaya, 21, a UCLA grad from Oakland,
Calif., drops her jaw. My God, he's standing naked in the pool. Not
the low Teck introduction she had in mind.
</P>
<P>
   Matt, a 22-year-old Southern Californian, is noticing Ruthie,
not Teck. When it comes time to pick roommates, Matt says, ``I want
to sleep in Ruthie's room.'' And he does, along with Amaya.
</P>
<P>
   ``It kind of feels like I'm living on a page of National
Geographic,'' Matt observes, thinking of all the bare bodies around
him.
</P>
<P>
   Kaia, 22, is a Chicagoan and UC Berkeley student. She gives the
impression of strength and levelheadedness.
</P>
<P>
   But Kaia, too, has a philosophical problem with attire. She
seems to regard a pair of panties as overdressed. ``I really,
really like looking at myself,'' Kaia says. ``Call it narcissistic
if you want.''
</P>
<P>
   OK. It's narcissistic.
</P>
<P>
   Justin, 21, is the brains of this year's crew. He's taking time
off from Harvard Law to be on ``The Real World.'' Justin is also
gay.
</P>
<P>
   I do not dislike Justin. But Justin has some challenging months
ahead of him. His roomie is Colin, 19, another UC Berkeley student.
Colin's just a bit perplexed by this gay thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't mind if I sleep naked, do you?'' Colin asks Justin.
Colin will take the top bunk.
</P>
<P>
   That's what happens Tuesday night. Oh, there's also the matter
of the ambulance.
</P>
<P>
   As soon as they're settled in, the cast goes out partying at a
nearby bar. Ruthie promptly drinks herself into a stupor. And what
a profound stupor it is _ eyes rolled back in her head, limbs
akimbo, brain shut down for repairs.
</P>
<P>
   They get her home, stand her up in the shower and tell her to
throw up. Then they call the ambulance. Whoosh, Ruthie's off to the
hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Yep, it's one more season of prime American youth.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &QL;  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
