<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Though perhaps not a place where people
spend ``most of their time,'' the Internet has affected how many
people do business, and the business of religion is increasingly no
exception. More Christians are going online, changing the ways that
spiritual communities interact and discuss matters of the soul. By
TARA DOOLEY. Story will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
