<P>
   CHAPMAN-TEXAS AT LARGE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Quitaque is a small, hard-to-spell community of 500
that sits just beneath the Caprock in Northwest Texas. For most of
the year, people don't pay much attention to the town, unless they
go to Caprock Canyon State Park to see the buffalo, or pass through
on the way to Turkey for Bob Wills Days. But early each June,
Quitaque makes headlines with its annual National Trails Day
celebration and the controversial guinea drop that goes with it. By
ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
