   JAIL-ART &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ALBANY, Texas _ The Old Jail Art Center has added a unique twist
to its profile of candidates for the next museum director's job:
It's looking for an executive who can talk cattle as well as art.
Situated in the historic cattle and oil town of Albany _ about an
hour east of Abilene _ the Old Jail has been without an executive
director since January, when Joeliene Magoto resigned to accept a
post that would take her closer to her family in Ohio. By JANET
TYSON. Story has moved in ``e'' arts and entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
