   EBAY-ADDICT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Stop me before I double-click again. My eyes are
bloodshot, my wrists are sore and my back aches. But I'm so
entranced, I can't stop. My husband's car breaks down, and he has
to walk three miles in 90-degree heat because he can't call home,
the line is busy. I'm making a buy. It started, like most habits
do, with curiosity. One online purchase certainly wouldn't be a
gateway to sin. One hundred personal checks later proves otherwise.
I'm an eBay junkie _ addicted to an auction house in cyberspace. By
BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle category.
(Accompanied by EBAY-ESSENTIALS.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In the winter of 1973, my mother died of a massive
heart attack. I was 15. She was 43. I always figured my mother died
before her time, and without time for her or those whom she loved
to prepare for her passing. More than 25 years later, I can't help
but wonder if it was a sick heart that killed her or simply a
lonely and unhappy one. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story has moved in
``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
