   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Son, I am going to take you to get a haircut today
AND wait, wait, wait a minute before you start looking for
someplace to hide. I promise on your turtle's grave that I will not
let them put fire on your neck.'' That's the script, and you have
to say it just like that or the boy will not cooperate. He hates to
go to the barber. By MONICA FRAZIER ANDERSON. Story has moved in
``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
