<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-NOTES _ HOUSTON _ Braves notebook. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   BBC-BATS _ Last year, USC beat Arizona State 21-14 _ more like a
football game than the final game in the College World Series. The
offensive show so startled the NCAA that new rules limiting the
size, weight and shape of aluminum bats were ordered for this
season. The smaller bats are being produced by Gayston Corp. of
Springboro, under contract for Rawlings. It presently accounts for
15 percent of the company's annual volume (also makes weapon
components, automobile air bag parts).This year, offensive
production is down and the restricted bat produced by Gayston is
coming under fire at this week's College World Series. Interviewed
Eastern Michigan University/New York Yankees catcher Michael
Aldridge of Franklin on the bat's impact. (Jackson, Dayton Daily
News). 12-14. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NBA-FINALS _ SAN ANTONIO _ The Spurs, who swept through
their last two seasons and have won 41 of their last 47 games, are
favorites in the NBA Finals beginning Wednesday. But the Knicks,
with the highest payroll in the league, belong, too, despite their
No. 8 seed in the East. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SPURS _ SAN ANTONIO _ Merchandise is selling fast, but they
expect the biggest rush to start today as tourists roll in. City
hotels are at full occupancy, alcohol sales are up. The city's
hoping the NBA Finals, coming just a year after the city hosted the
NCAA Final Four, will boost the city's growth and national
exposure. (Cocks, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DUNCAN _ Profile of Spurs star Tim Duncan and his childhood
roots in the Virgin Islands. (D'Angelo, Palm Beach Post). WITH MAP,
ILLUSTRATION. 21.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MARINO _ Dan Marino signs two-year contraact extension. 18
inches. (Clarke, Plam Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-CAMP _ Coverage of Falcons optional passing camp.
(Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ Notebook from Falcons optional passing camp.
(Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BENGALS-CAMP _ Story off first day of minicamp. (Williams,
Dayton Daily News). 15.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MONTY _ ATLANTA _When he's in his element in European _
cloudy cool conditions, home turf courses _ Colin Montgomerie has
been unbeatable. He enters the U.S. Open as one of the hottest
golfers on earth. But when Monty steps out of his element and comes
to the U.S., success has been slow to follow. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
