<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-KLA _ STARIE KACANEK, Kosovo _ The KLA flexes its mucle.
Hundreds of Serb civilians, fearing for their lives, fled this town
Tuesday after it was taken over by Kosovo Liberation Army rebels
who discovered a mass grave. The KLA fighters, angered by
eyewitness accounts of how Serb soldiers had executed Kosovar
residents, began firing their weapons in the air and ordered the
Serb residents to leave. About 30 carloads of Serbs soon fled. It
may be the first documented case of ethnic cleansing by ethnic
Albanians and illustrates the difficulty NATO peacekeepers will
have in preventing acts of revenge. And for the first time in a
year, KLA commander Drini was able to come into town, have coffe
and along the way declare that this is the first city that the KLA
controls ``100 percent.'' He said the KLA will cooperate with the
Military-Technical Agreement but are not prepared de-militarize.
The German NATO commanders in the area say that they are not going
to crack down on the rebel fighters at this point.
(Albright-Kaplow, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PEC _ PEC, Yugoslavia _ This city that is the center of
Serbian Orthodoxy look like a ghost town. Home to Serbia's largest
Orthodox Church, the core of downtown is virtually untouched, the
only people visible on Tuedsay were a dozen Serb men sitting on a
park bench. In a region that saw the worst of the Serb ethnic
cleansing campaign, the efficiency of that campaign in Pec is
frightening. Developing.
</P>
<P>
   (Kaplow, Cox News Service) 20.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SERBS _ PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ The first phase of the
11-day withdrawal of Serb-led Yugoslav troops from Kosovo province
looked as though it would wrap up right on schedule Tuesday _ with
little incident. It's what the Serb troops are leaving behind
that's causing concern and consternation. Ethnic Albanians are
coming down from the mountains to return to their homes and finding
looted, burned-out husks. They watch as they wait for the Serb
troops to depart, and see them taking their belongings, throwing
appliances out the door, clothes ripped up and their property
defecated on. Developing. (Kunstel, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
