   GOD-SIGNS _ What's up with all those new billboards signed by
God? They're a national PSA campaign, which has been embraced by 2
of the big billboard companies in Atlanta. (Harris, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRONG-CONVICTION _ Sixteen years after he was sent to prison
after he was convicted of rape in Clayton County, Calvin Johnson
was to be back in court Tuesday, asking to be freed. New DNA tests
cleared him. Johnson was sentenced to life in prison after trials
in Clayton and Fulton counties on two different rape incidents. He
was convicted in Clayton and acquitted in Fulton. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
