<P>
   TRAVEL-BRIEFS (Undated) _ Nero's stately pleasure dome reopens;
Summer flower shows multiply in England; Disney raises prices,
other parks follow. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Travel questions and answers: Glasgow
design fete; Hemingway Key West bash; Introduction to Agrigento. By
Suzanne MacNeille. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   PRACTICAL-TRAVELER (Undated) _ Hotel phone bill can be a shock.
By Betsy Wade. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   CYBER-TRAVEL (Undated) _ Surfing the Net: Smithsonian tours;
easy navigating. By L. R. Shannon. (Moved.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LONDON-TAXIS (London) _ Cabless in London: Stranded after
dark. By Alan Cowell. (Moved.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-FRENCH-ALPS (Megeve, France) _ A faux Savoy village in
the French resort of Megeve makes a charming base for outings into
the surrounding mountains. By Glenn Collins. (Moved.)
