<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAU-DONATE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CAU receives $1 million grant
 &HT;    By Tammy Joyner
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Clark Atlanta University has received a $1 million
grant from the Lilly Endowment/United Negro College Fund to enhance
its computer technology program and develop a distance-learning
center.
</P>
<P>
   The historically black college was one of several that received
part of a $41.7 million grant, the largest single grant in the
61-year history of the endowment.
</P>
<P>
   ``Improved technology gives the university the opportunity to
improve its services and academic programs,'' said Clark Atlanta
President Thomas Cole Jr., also chairman of the UNCF Council of
Presidents.
</P>
<P>
   The money will enable the school to make improvements to its
interactive computer labs and extend the reach of the school's
curriculum.
</P>
<P>
   The Lilly endowment also will enable the school to set up a
Distance Learning Center that will teach faculty and staff about
various multimedia technology _ the Web, videotape and interactive
videoconferencing _ used in distance learning.
</P>
<P>
   Increasingly, schools are using distance learning to extend
programs outside their geographic area.
</P>
<P>
   Additionally, the grant will help the school complete its
installation of BANNER, an integrated computer system that will
replace the three software systems now used at the university.
</P>
<P>
   The project is expected to be completed by spring 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Currently, separate computer systems serve finance and payroll,
student accounts and registration, and alumni functions.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will be able to take a student's application from
acceptance to registration and enrollment, maintain grades and
financial information through graduation and beyond,'' said Winfred
Harris, provost and vice president of academic affairs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Once a student's information is put into the BANNER database,
it will remain for a lifetime.''
</P>
<P>
   Lilly Endowment is an Indianapolis-based, private philanthropic
foundation created in 1937.
</P>
<P>
   Tammy Joyner writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
