   &UR; SETTLEMENT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-RUSSIANS (Moscow) _ The Russian troops who sprinted into
Kosovo last weekend ahead of NATO provided a brief surge of
national pride for a country that has grown used to seeing its
once-proud military humiliated. Tuesday, however, things began to
drift back to normal. By David Filipov. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PHYSICIANS (Boston) _ Physician rights group says the
Serbs engaged in systematic acts of violence against Kosovar
Albanians, especially health care professionals. By James Bandler.
700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-TRIP (Paris) _ President Clinton begins a seven-day
European tour amid the afterglow of NATO's victory in Yugoslavia,
but beset by a dispute with Russia over control of its troops. By
Ann Scales. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-GORE (Providence, R.I.) _ After seven years as the
understudy to President Clinton, Al Gore is eager to establish his
own identity. He makes his formal announcement of candidacy
Wednesday. By Ann Scales. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-BUSH (Undated) _ His policies are still fuzzy, but
George W. Bush shows he can win crowds. People strain to get near
the front-runner for the GOP presidential nomination. By Jill
Zuckman. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-ANALYSIS (Manchester, N.H.) _ One thing that comes through
loud and clear as Bush tours the region: He is making few
accommodations to the right flank. By Michael Kranish. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   NY-GIULIANI (New York) _ Before he runs for the Senate, Rudolph
Giuliani needs to get rid of Mark Green, who would automatically
succeed him if he is elected. Green is an old-guard liberal whom
Giuliani hates. By Fred Kaplan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-TEACHER-CERTIFY (Boston) _ Conceding that a six-year-old
effort to improve teacher quality has been misguided, state
officials are proposing to change a controversial law that requires
teachers to renew their certification every five years. By Kate
Zernike and Doreen Iudica Vigue. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-NO-COD (Chatham, Mass.) _ New federal cod-fishing limits that
take effect July 1 could create a nightmare for Cape Cod eateries
that usually tout their fresh catch. By Ellen O'Brien. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   UTILITY-DEALS (Undated) _ It was a huge day for utility deals in
New England. New York group buys Central Maine Power for $957
million; Northeast Utilities announces merger with Yankee Energy
Systems. This leaves virtually no merger partner left in the region
for Boston Edison. By Peter Howe. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   AKAMIA-WEB (Undated) _ Akamai Technologies inks deals with 20
major Web site companies, including CNN and Disney's Go Network.
Akamai will use a new technology developed by MIT mathematicians to
speed up delivery of pictures, video and sound over the Internet.
By Hiawatha Bray. 500 words.
</P>
