<P>
   KOSOVO-GRAVES (Djakovica/Velika Krusa, Yugoslavia) _ The Serbs'
most brutal force in their campaign to drive out Kosovo's ethnic
Albanian majority fell on this city and a swath of villages around
it in the shadow of the Accursed Mountains. On Tuesday, in a
landscape of gravesites, burned homes, toppled mosque minarets and
smashed shops it became clear just how ferocious that campaign had
been. By John Kifner and Ian Fisher. By John Kifner and Ian Fisher.
