<P>
   KOSOVO-EUROPE (Paris) _ The war in Kosovo obscured something of
a revolution in another part of Europe. Over the past few months,
the leaders of Britain and Germany have formalized a centrist,
Clinton-style manifesto to further distance their leftist parties
from decades of higher taxes, stringent government economic
controls and a social welfare system that is cushy by American
standards. By CRAGG HINES. (Already filed.)
