   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Derry, N.H.) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush sat down at
a picnic table to join some workers at Hadco Industries and was
instantly joined by dozens of camera crews. ``Mind if I join you?''
Bush asked the workers. ``That is, me and my 200 new best
friends?'' Charmed by the Republican presidential candidate, the
workers resigned their quiet coffee break to the national
spotlight. ``Seems like a nice guy,'' said one worker. ``But I'd
like to hear where he stands on the issues.'' By JOHN C. HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERN-BAPTISTS (Atlanta) _ At their national meeting in
