<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ When the Supreme Court ruled that
school boards may be held liable if they do nothing to stop the
sexual harassment of one student by another, there were loud wails
that the decision would spawn endless expensive lawsuits on a
matter that was no business of the schools anyway. But to have
ignored the problem would have sent a signal that anything goes,
and that could have terrible consequences. By MARIANNE MEANS.
(Already filed.)
