<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-SILICON-VALLEY-NYT, which moved
in ``f'' news file.)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``There are some people who are making the case that the
Internet has changed the law of physics. But this is still a
Newtonian world, and when you throw something up in this world,
it's going to come down.''
</P>
<P>
   _FRED HOAR, anticipating a shift, at some point, in Silocon
Valley's fortunes.
</P>
</TEXT>
