in Derry on Tuesday as part of his first presidential campaign
swing. Bush was showered with $1.3 million at a dinner crowning him
the adopted favorite son of Greenwich, which considers itself
ground zero for Bushes although the candidate himself has never
lived here. (Andrea Mohin/New York Times Photo)
