Polisario Front, fighting for independence, takes time to pray
facing Mecca, thousands of miles away. Once an oasis for camel
trains, the whitewashed billets here are now an outpost of a
guerrilla force that has spent most of the last decade idled in the
desert, waiting out a cease-fire that ended 16 years of war with
Morocco. (John Giannini/New York Times Photo)
