destroyed by Yugoslav forces. The Serbs most brutal force in their
campaign to drive out Kosovo's ethnic Albanian majority fell on
this city and a swath of villages around it in the shadow of the
Accursed Mountains. Today, in a landscape of mass graves, burned
homes, toppled mosque minarets and smashed shops it became clear
just how brutal that campaign had been. (Stephen Crowley/New York
Times Photo)
