company. In the midst of the longest sustained boom in the nation's
high-technology heartland, there is a palpable air of unreality
that has come to color the outlook Silicon Valley's rank and file.
Lane complained recently that local dealerships had a six-month
waiting list for the Porsche so he had to find his elsewhere using
the Internet. (Peter DaSilva/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) BELA CRKVA, Yugoslavia -- June 15, 1999 --
KOSOVO-GRAVES-4, 6-15 -- Ethnic Albanian Teki Zhuniqi stands inside
