campaign to drive out Kosovo's ethnic Albanian majority fell in
this region in the shadow of the Accursed Mountains. Today, in a
landscape of mass graves, burned homes, toppled mosque minarets and
smashed shops, it became clear just how brutal that campaign had
been. (Tyler Hicks/New York Times Photo)
