<P>
   (NYT1) CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- June 15, 1999 -- BLACK-ANCESTORS-BOS,
6-15 -- Mario Valdes, a genealogist, sits under a print of
England's Queen Charlotte, who died in 1818, at his home earlier
this month. In his latest genealogical effort, Valdes exposes the
alleged black roots of England's Queen Elizabeth. The key to
Valdes's claims about Queen Elizabeth is the family tree he charted
of England's Queen Charlotte who has been rumored for nearly two
centuries to be a direct descendant of a black woman. (Michael
Robinson-Chavez/Boston Globe Photo) LITE
</P>
