<HEADLINE>
UCLA LANDS FIFTH RECRUIT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA landed its fifth recruit of the season last
weekend when Las Vegas center John Ream gave the Bruins a verbal
commitment.
</P>
<P>
   Ream, a rising senior at Chapparal High School, is 6-4 and 285
pounds. He received scholarship offers from both Arizona schools,
Oregon and Nebraska.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins have approximately 17 scholarships available, and
they hope to sign several offensive linemen to bolster a unit
depleted by injuries (Jeff Wright, Scott Wiegand), position change
(Steve Morgan) and academic trouble (Dave Wilford).
</P>
<P>
   Ream attended UCLA's one-day camp Saturday but did not
participate. Perhaps the best player was Sacramento receiver Willie
Dixon, who is considering UCLA and Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   Strong sales: There's no Heisman Trophy candidate, no lofty
preseason ranking and no opponent as strong as Texas tailback Ricky
Williams on the schedule. But business is brisk at UCLA's ticket
office.
</P>
<P>
   Through June 10, the Bruins were 2,900 season tickets ahead of
last year's pace, when they sold 34,400 _ the second-highest total
in school history, according to marketing director Scott Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a bigger base than we did last year,'' Mitchell said.
``But not having Cade (McNown) and with the quarterback uncertain,
that plays in the back of people's minds. A lot of people will make
their mind up in August.''
</P>
<P>
   Watch for radio spots and freeway billboards to appear next
month. The Bruins are using a ``Do You Believe?'' marketing theme,
with a photo of All-American receiver Danny Farmer making a diving,
one-handed catch.
</P>
<P>
   Odds and ends: UCLA opens with Boise State in the Rose Bowl on
Sept. 4 (Labor day weekend). Be prepared for a 7 p.m. kickoff.
</P>
<P>
   Fresno State (Sept. 18) is the other nonconference home game.
</P>
<P>
   Continuing its renovation project, the Rose Bowl has added
concession stands and parking since last season, Mitchell said.
</P>
<P>
   Get your tickets now: Coach Bob Toledo should have his best team
in 2000, when the Bruins host Alabama and Michigan.
</P>
<P>
   Ticket information: 310-UCLA-WIN.
</P>
</TEXT>
