<SLUG> BC-IMAGE-LOSS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IMAGE MAY REFLECT A LOSS THIS QUARTER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DAVE McNARY  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Image Entertainment, scrambling to transform
itself from laserdisc to DVD supplier, announced Tuesday that it
might post a loss in the current quarter due to problems at its new
Las Vegas warehouse.
</P>
<P>
   Image made the announcement after the market closed and could
see a sell-off Wednesday. The stock, off 25 cents at $7.50 on
Tuesday, has traded under $4 and over $11 during the past year.
</P>
<P>
   Image closed down its warehouse in suburban Chatsworth six weeks
ago when it opened a state-of-the-art, 76,000-square-foot facility
in Las Vegas. The new plant originally was slated to open last year
but software delays held up the opening.
</P>
<P>
   Image said implementing software at the new plant has been
slower than anticipated, leading to shortfalls in meeting orders
and a possible loss in its first quarter ending June 30. It said
the plant will match the efficiency of Chatsworth _ shipping within
48 hours _ in July and reach its goal of shipping in under 24 hours
by August.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am confident that when Las Vegas is operating at its planned
level of efficiency, it will allow us to take advantage of the
continued growth I foresee in the DVD market,'' said Martin
Greenwald, president and chief executive officer.
</P>
<P>
   After the market closed Tuesday, Image also reported a
fourth-quarter profit of $1.05 million, or 7 cents a share,
compared with a loss of $10.3 million due to a writedown for
laserdisc assets. Sales rose 45 percent to $23 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
